<br>
If the race is to kill a single 32k mob, 6 wizzies win.  If the goal is to take down ALL the 32k mobs in the shortest possible time, I would put my money on the balanced group every time.<br>
<br>
The 6 wizzies outdo the group massively in the instant-damage category, but isn't that what wizards are all about? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubaelzharon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baelzharon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 459<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/11/02 11:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: turnaround time</span><hr size=1> God a 33% damage spell would be too powerful. When you got mobs in VT with a few million Hp's the damage 3 of 4 wizards would do would make the encounter trivial. Even a 5% damage spell at that range would be insane amounts of damage (100,000+). <br>
