Of course, this does make the assumption that the mana bar is full in the first place, a constraint that HT does not have. It also uses all remaining mana when you use it, another constraint that HT doesn't have. It also has a casting time and is interruptable, something else that HT doesn't suffer from. Also, you don't actually get to use it til you are at least level 59, again, a constraint that HT doesn't share. It also takes AA points, strange, but again this is something that HT doesn't take. So why even bring up HT when you are talking about MB? <p><a target="_blank" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380>Qaman</a><BR>
