You are also missing that there are several /disc and AA skill for increasing the HT effect. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uswipey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swipey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/6/02 4:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The real nerf will be ..</span><hr size=1> Quaman :<br>
I brought up HT because of Grimstaff's response to Sililea.  <br>
<br>
Sililea said it seemed unbalanced in PvP that a wizard can kill a full health character with a single attack using MB, Grimstaff responded that SKs could do that, so why was she complaining?<br>
<br>
I have (gasp) made the assumption that Grimstaff was referring to Harm Touch, hence the talk about Harm Touch.<br>
<br>
<br>
Znail :<br>
As for the increased damage on HT via Disciplines, yeah, I missed that one.  50% increase at level 55 using Unholy Aura.  Alt Advancement, however, does not add actual damage to HT, currently.  The two AAs that effect an SKs Touch are Leechtouch, which allows the HT to act as a lifetap (target loses, SK gains), and Super HT, which is a harder to resist HT.  Neither AA touch can be used with Unholy Aura, or with eachother.<br>
<br>
So HT max at level 60 isnt 801, its 1202.  Still considerably less than the 3200+ MB can pump out, and not enough to one-shot a healthy opponent.<br>
<br>
As to the &quot;HT is instant and MB takes 6 seconds to cast&quot; response to how you figure HT DPS is higher then MB DPS, are you saying that I should divide MB damage by 6 to get its DPS, and then divide HT damage by 0, or what?  <br>
